</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1417,2122,883,916]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="22.[1417,2622,725,1115]" box="[1417,2122,883,916]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1417,1652,883,916]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Himalayan Mole is fossorial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="617" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[1417,2622,725,1115]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1419,2142,926,955]" pageId="22" pageNumber="617">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Tunnels of the Himalayan Mole extend 30-40 m, and burrows are 9-15 cm in diameter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
